  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The synchronous speed (\\(N_s\\)) of an AC motor can be calculated using the following formula:\n\n\\[\nN_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P}\n\\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\(N_s\\) = synchronous speed in revolutions per minute (RPM)\n- \\(f\\) = frequency of the AC supply in hertz (Hz)\n- \\(P\\) = number of poles in the motor\n\nThis formula indicates that the synchronous speed increases with an increase in frequency and decreases with an increase in the number of poles.",
